<article class="PUT docs-container">
  <header class="header-bg-dark d-sm-flex justify-content-sm-between
                align-items-sm-center py-2 px-3">
    <h2 class="pb-2 pb-sm-0 m-0">Update a Misc Ingredient</h2>
    <code class="m-0">
      <b>PUT</b> /misc_ingredients/:id
    </code>
  </header>

  <section class="p-3 inner-docs-container">
    <p>This method allows users to retrieve and edit a specific miscelaneous ingredient.</p>

    <h3 class="subheader-bold">Request</h3>

    <p>https://theteaapi.herokuapp.com/api/v1/misc_ingredients/<em>:id</em></p>
    <p>OR</p>
    <p>https://theteaapi.herokuapp.com/api/v1/misc_ingredients/<em>misc-ingredient-name</em></p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        The headers must include a valid authentication token.
      </li>
      <li>
        :id is the id the misc ingredient to update. You can also use the
        miscelaneous ingredient's name.
      </li>
      <li>
        The body canâ€™t be empty and must include the name attribute,
        a string that will be used as the name of the miscelaneous ingredient.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      <code>
    {
      "id": 3,
      "name": "changing my new misc ingredient"
    }
      </code>
    </p>

    <h3 class="subheader-bold">Response</h3>

    <p>If succeeds, returns the updated miscelaneous ingredient.</p>

    <p>
      <code>
    Status: 200 OK
      </code>
      <code>
    {
      "id": 3,
      "name": "changing my new misc ingredient"
    }
      </code>
    </p>
  </section>
</article>
